  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/182",
  "title": "instantjs always fires a search",
  "body": "Hi,\n\nI'm currently using a _searchBox_ and a _hits_ widget for a documentation search box.\n\nCurrently instantjs fires a search with an empty input on page load. It would be great to have some sort of switch or, even better, a **character threshold** parameter with a reasonable default value (_e.g. Don't fire a search request for less than three characters_) like Typeahead.js does.\n\nA possible implementation could be adding a `minLength` parameter on the _searchBox_ widget:\n\n``` javascript\nsearch.addWidget({\n  container: '#search-wrapper input',\n  minLength: 3\n});\n```\n",
